8 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending 68
O.S. 2021, Section 3634, which relates to the Filmed
10 in Oklahoma Act of 2021; modifying provisions related
to expenditure requirements for incentive
11 eligibility; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
12
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3634, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 3634. A. The total amount of rebate payments
20 conditionally pre-qualified by the Department of Commerce each
21 fiscal year with respect to any of the incentives authorized
22 pursuant to this act shall not exceed Thirty Million Dollars
23 ($30,000,000.00). Projects not conditionally pre-qualified for
24 rebate payments due to the limitations provided in this section may
Req. No. 16594 Page 1

1 be c onditionally pre-qualified by the Department in subsequent
2 fiscal years.
3 B. The amount of rebate payments conditionally pre-qualified by
4 the Department of Commerce each fiscal year with respect to any of
5 the incentives authorized pursuant to this act shall not exceed:
6 1. Seven Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00)
7 for production projects with total expenditures of less than Seven
8 Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00); and
9 2. Twenty-two Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
10 ($22,500,000.00) for production projects with total expenditures of
11 Seven Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($7,500,000.00) or more.
12 C. A production project shall have total expenditures of Fifty
13 Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) or more to be eligible for the rebate
14 payments provided in this act or Twenty Thousand Dollars
15 ($20,000.00) for projects filmed outside this state as provided for
16 in Section 3636 of this title.
17 D. In any fiscal year if the amount of rebate payments
18 conditionally pre-qualified by the Department of Commerce are less
19 than the limitations provided in this section, the excess rebate
20 payments not utilized shall be added to subsequent fiscal year's
21 limitation.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
Req. No. 16594 Page 2

1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
